On National Former Prisoner of War Recognition Day, President Donald Trump honors the service men and women who were imprisoned during war. He acknowledges their sacrifices and devotion to the country. The proclamation also mentions the 75th anniversary of the Bataan Death March, where American and Filipino soldiers were subjected to extreme conditions and many lost their lives. The President expresses his commitment to supporting and caring for veterans, especially former POWs. He calls upon Americans and government officials to observe the day and honor the sacrifice of all former prisoners of war.